  {
    "name": "projects/readative-803b0/databases/(default)/documents/smarttalk/VdXBYzEW3BB6ho8fUDJT",
    "fields": {
      "authorId": {
        "stringValue": "guest_5gstjkokr"
      },
      "answers": {
        "arrayValue": {
          "values": [
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777361829286"
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_5gstjkokr"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "In my experience, having two screens is a total lifesaver for my job. I usually keep my email or chat open on one and my actual work on the other. It saves so much time because I do not have to click back and forth. If you want to try it, [Dell Monitors](https://www.dell.com/en-us/shop/monitors-monitor-accessories/ac/4009) are a good place to start looking for a second display."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "83v8ty13g"
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "zain"
                  },
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {
                      "values": [
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_5gstjkokr"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "wGp2Tb5R6Mcfw7N34sXQnimb9PS2"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "jehnzgarz"
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "divansh217867"
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_5gstjkokr"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "To be honest, I think two screens just make you lose focus. I tried it for a month and found that I spent more time looking at videos than actually working. I went back to just one screen and I am much faster now. I actually watched a helpful guide on [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/) about how to stay focused with less stuff on your desk."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777361885491"
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777361963364"
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_5gstjkokr"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "Actually, the best way is to get one giant 'ultrawide' screen and use a special tool to split it into parts. I use [FancyZones](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/powertoys/fancyzones) to snap my windows into place perfectly. It feels like having three screens but without all the messy wires and cables everywhere."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {
                      "values": [
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_i6u73kegk"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "c4r4kjb1x"
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "tech-ronny"
                  },
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {
                      "values": [
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_5gstjkokr"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_tg5tkxqu5"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "Two screens help because you can keep your main task on one display and references or chat on the other, which reduces window switching and mental friction while working."
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_pez5ae7wq"
                  },
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777455493030"
                  },
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "35jxwkuio"
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "codextest"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "content": {
        "stringValue": "Is it actually better to have two computer screens or is one big screen enough for most people?"
      },
      "createdAt": {
        "timestampValue": "2026-04-28T07:36:28.214Z"
      },
      "aiAnswered": {
        "booleanValue": false
      },
      "author": {
        "stringValue": "jay"
      }
    },
    "createTime": "2026-04-28T07:36:28.225773Z",
    "updateTime": "2026-05-07T08:33:00.661293Z"
  },
  {
    "name": "projects/readative-803b0/databases/(default)/documents/smarttalk/jCgVk2mhZXDwKiNKsRRp",
    "fields": {
      "author": {
        "stringValue": "yash.nalawade"
      },
      "aiAnswered": {
        "booleanValue": false
      },
      "createdAt": {
        "timestampValue": "2026-04-27T07:05:39.161Z"
      },
      "answers": {
        "arrayValue": {
          "values": [
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777273592493"
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "I honestly believe we are in a new era where the 'how' matters less than the 'what.' In my experience, AI is like a superpower that lets you skip the boring parts of learning. I used this for a recent project where I built a website without knowing much CSS, and it turned out great. I recommend jumping straight into building things and letting the tools help you. Check out Replit to see how easy it is to start a project from scratch today."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "5tgoeod20"
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "TechGeek"
                  },
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {
                      "values": [
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_tg5tkxqu5"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_bn93lf9om"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_rivqqb3dk"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_mb7k5op02"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_ql1s9wqfn"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_i6u73kegk"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "2pndnoxlw"
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "Ryan"
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "To be honest, I am a bit skeptical of people saying you don't need to learn the basics. Actually, I have seen AI generate code that looks perfect but is totally broken. If you don't have the foundation, you won't know how to fix it when things go sideways. I found that I still spend a lot of time on Stack Overflow double-checking what the AI tells me. It is a tool, not a replacement for your brain."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777273630053"
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777273850020"
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "I actually just started my first coding course, and I found that having an AI help me explain lines of code makes the learning process so much faster. It's not a waste of time because you need to know how to talk to the AI. I used a site called Codecademy to get the basics down, and now I use AI to help me with the homework. It feels like having a tutor right next to me 24/7."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "mi6iklt0k"
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "Jen"
                  },
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "Call me old-fashioned, but I think skipping the basics is a huge mistake. Relying on a machine to think for you makes your skills weak. In my experience, there is a grit you develop when you have to solve a problem with just a book and your own head. I still buy physical books from Amazon to learn new things because it forces me to focus and actually retain the knowledge without a shortcut."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777273910548"
                  },
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "Gvincr26"
                  },
                  "id": {
