  {
    "name": "projects/readative-803b0/databases/(default)/documents/smarttalk/uhiEkeN2mXgwqyIQ3Uyb",
    "fields": {
      "author": {
        "stringValue": "Farhan"
      },
      "authorId": {
        "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
      },
      "content": {
        "stringValue": "Is AI actually going to kill human creativity, or are we just overhyping a fancy autocomplete tool?"
      },
      "answers": {
        "arrayValue": {
          "values": [
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {
                      "values": [
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_tg5tkxqu5"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_rivqqb3dk"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_ql1s9wqfn"
                        },
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_i6u73kegk"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "43ikszo9y"
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "Marcus"
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "I use AI every single day for my job as a designer. In my experience, it is not even close to replacing a human. I recommend looking at it like a digital intern. It can handle the boring stuff like resizing images or checking for basic errors, but it has no taste. I found that I spend way more time on the 'soul' of the project now because I am not stuck doing the repetitive tasks. Check out how I use it with Adobe Firefly to speed up my workflow."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {
                      "values": [
                        {
                          "stringValue": "guest_mb7k5op02"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777273114264"
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "To be honest, I was really worried at first, but after playing with a few tools, I am less scared. AI is just a mirror of what is already on the internet. Actually, I tried to make it write a short story and it was so generic that I almost fell asleep. It lacks that weird, human perspective that makes art interesting. I tried Midjourney and while the pictures are pretty, they all start to look the same after a while."
                  },
                  "dislikes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777273173018"
                  },
                  "likes": {
                    "arrayValue": {}
                  },
                  "author": {
                    "stringValue": "Brad"
                  },
                  "id": {
                    "stringValue": "cyfw3aa22"
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "mapValue": {
                "fields": {
                  "createdAt": {
                    "integerValue": "1777273231718"
                  },
                  "authorId": {
                    "stringValue": "guest_63hw91gyk"
                  },
                  "content": {
                    "stringValue": "I just figured out how to use these tools last week and I am honestly blown away. I used to be terrified of writing professional emails, but now I use Grammarly to make sure I don't sound like a total mess. It has actually helped me learn how to write better myself because I see the corrections it makes in real-time. If you are a beginner like me, I recommend just starting small."
                  },
